# Lab 07-1 — Veterinary App

A Ruby on Rails application for managing a veterinary clinic. Includes owners, pets, vets, appointments, and treatments with rich text support.

## Setup & Running

```bash
bundle install
bin/rails db:setup
bin/rails server
```

Then open http://localhost:3000 in your browser.

## System Dependencies

### libvips (required for image variants)

Active Storage uses libvips to generate image variants (e.g. the 60×60 thumbnails on the Pet index page).

**macOS:**
```bash
brew install vips
```

**Ubuntu / Debian:**
```bash
sudo apt-get install libvips-dev
```

**Arch Linux:**
```bash
sudo pacman -S libvips
```

## Trix Sanitization Check

Pasted `<script>alert(1)</script>` into the Trix editor on the Treatment form and saved. On the Appointment show page, no alert fired and the script tag did not appear in the rendered HTML — Action Text strips it automatically.
